1
00:00:14,425 --> 00:00:19,863
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,698 --> 00:00:28,605
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,673 --> 00:00:34,043
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,112 --> 00:00:38,173
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,417 --> 00:00:44,320
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,056 --> 00:00:51,962
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,364 --> 00:00:56,856
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,935 --> 00:01:03,841
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,975 --> 00:01:11,040
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,115 --> 00:01:17,782
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,189 --> 00:01:27,757
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:55,037 --> 00:01:57,062
<i>The smell is moving away...</i>

13
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:01,173
I'm saved...

14
00:02:02,177 --> 00:02:03,109
<i>Who is?</i>

15
00:02:14,523 --> 00:02:16,047
Please wait!

16
00:02:17,759 --> 00:02:20,421
The real deal... starts now!

17
00:02:23,966 --> 00:02:28,960
<i>My role now is to stall this person</i>
<i>as long as possible...</i>

18
00:02:29,037 --> 00:02:33,235
<i>so, I should've avoided big techniques</i>
<i>that could be self defeating...</i>

19
00:02:34,810 --> 00:02:37,404
<i>But it seems this isn't an opponent</i>
<i>easy enough to beat</i>

20
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:39,276
<i>without using my Secret Technique...</i>

21
00:02:42,751 --> 00:02:43,775
Here I go!

22
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:48,283
<i>I just had surgery</i>
<i>and am not at my best...</i>

23
00:02:48,357 --> 00:02:51,884
<i>But if it'd just be opening the first of the</i>
<i>Eight Inner Gates, the Gate of Opening,</i>

24
00:02:51,994 --> 00:02:52,858
<i>I should somehow...</i>

25
00:02:56,898 --> 00:02:59,162
The first gate... The Gate of Opening...

26
00:02:59,935 --> 00:03:00,424
Open!

27
00:03:03,872 --> 00:03:05,339
Primary Lotus!

28
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:14,978
<i>The impact of the kick</i>
<i>was suppressed by the bones...?!</i>

29
00:03:15,517 --> 00:03:19,681
That's some speed... But it's over.

30
00:03:20,756 --> 00:03:25,887
<i>Damn it... No matter how much I think,</i>
<i>I can't come up with any good strategies...!</i>

31
00:03:27,195 --> 00:03:31,063
<i>I've had it...can't hold any further...</i>

32
00:03:33,635 --> 00:03:37,401
With me right in front of you,
you can't even howl like a loser...?

33
00:03:38,507 --> 00:03:39,201
Huh?!

34
00:03:40,742 --> 00:03:41,504
Die!

35
00:03:42,878 --> 00:03:44,004
You're mine!

36
00:03:44,913 --> 00:03:47,404
Don't you be smiling
before you're going to die!

37
00:03:57,659 --> 00:03:58,626
What?!

38
00:04:06,468 --> 00:04:07,435
Who're you?!

39
00:04:14,643 --> 00:04:17,441
It seems you're an ally this time...

40
00:04:25,754 --> 00:04:26,686
Who're you?!

41
00:04:28,090 --> 00:04:29,717
A Sand...

42
00:04:30,726 --> 00:04:31,852
Shinobi...

43
00:04:32,327 --> 00:04:33,851
ally of the Leaf!

44
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:44,071
<i>The Sand Shinobi.</i>
<i>Allies of the Leaf</i>

45
00:04:58,386 --> 00:05:02,482
<i>The Sand...?! Am I still drunk...?</i>

46
00:05:16,304 --> 00:05:18,238
Gaara of the Desert...

47
00:05:25,413 --> 00:05:26,641
Gaara.

48
00:05:30,485 --> 00:05:31,975
Is that who you are?

49
00:05:34,756 --> 00:05:35,916
Digital Shrapnel!

50
00:05:59,881 --> 00:06:02,714
<i>Did he blow the finger tip bones...?!</i>

51
00:06:05,554 --> 00:06:07,021
Impetuous...

52
00:06:20,936 --> 00:06:21,994
You...

53
00:06:23,939 --> 00:06:28,467
When you fought me...
you had more speed and sharpness.

54
00:06:33,148 --> 00:06:34,775
Easy to say...

55
00:06:37,152 --> 00:06:39,484
It's not that I'm holding a grudge...

56
00:06:39,855 --> 00:06:44,656
But on account of you,
I had kind of a tough time of it.

57
00:06:47,829 --> 00:06:48,796
I see...

58
00:06:54,269 --> 00:06:56,362
But... why you?

59
00:06:58,974 --> 00:07:01,067
I owe a lot...

60
00:07:03,612 --> 00:07:05,546
to the Leaf.

61
00:07:07,182 --> 00:07:08,649
Sasuke!

62
00:07:15,924 --> 00:07:19,519
I heard that we'd made up
with the Sand traitors...

63
00:07:20,028 --> 00:07:22,496
But to think you'd change
this abruptly...

64
00:07:23,098 --> 00:07:26,864
It's not like we attacked the Leaf
for the fun of it...

65
00:07:27,802 --> 00:07:29,235
It was an order...

66
00:07:30,071 --> 00:07:32,835
In the same way
that I'm here now.

67
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:38,040
<i>I see. The Fifth Hokage</i>
<i>asked the Sand...</i>

68
00:07:38,446 --> 00:07:39,743
<i>It's a big help.</i>

69
00:07:40,949 --> 00:07:45,443
By the way...
has your sharpness gotten worse?

70
00:07:45,754 --> 00:07:46,448
Huh?

71
00:07:51,726 --> 00:07:54,058
Are you going to give up again
or something?

72
00:07:54,429 --> 00:07:56,727
This time, <i>I'll</i> do it for you!

73
00:07:57,632 --> 00:08:00,157
Sorry, but I can't give up.

74
00:08:00,735 --> 00:08:03,636
A man mustn't be protected
by a woman, so...

75
00:08:05,273 --> 00:08:08,106
As usual, you're a guy who's annoying
with the man and woman stuff.

76
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:11,477
Even if you act tough, it's totally obvious
that it's bravado, you idiot!

77
00:08:21,456 --> 00:08:23,515
This time you're taking sides
with the Leaf, huh?!

78
00:08:23,591 --> 00:08:26,253
You guys sure are busy
all over the place!

79
00:08:27,662 --> 00:08:29,755
She uses Genjutsu
with the sound of her flute.

80
00:08:29,831 --> 00:08:30,729
Right!

81
00:08:37,105 --> 00:08:39,198
Cyclone Scythe Jutsu!

82
00:08:52,821 --> 00:08:54,721
<i>Blowing away the sounds of the flute</i>

83
00:08:54,789 --> 00:08:57,622
<i>and being able to nail the opponent</i>
<i>with a physical attack.</i>

84
00:08:57,859 --> 00:08:59,918
<i>To think she can attack and defend</i>
<i>with one hand...</i>

85
00:08:59,995 --> 00:09:02,691
<i>Unlike me, she has a nice Jutsu.</i>

86
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,908
<i>That woman's a natural enemy to me!</i>

87
00:09:37,499 --> 00:09:41,902
Has Ukon... just about caught him
according to the strategy?

88
00:09:53,281 --> 00:09:54,976
Puppet, huh?

89
00:09:58,186 --> 00:10:01,815
You three had been approaching
together, right?

90
00:10:02,190 --> 00:10:03,782
Two went on ahead.

91
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:05,956
You guys are weak, so...

92
00:10:06,761 --> 00:10:09,662
You idiot... These guys are
out of the ordinary!

93
00:10:13,301 --> 00:10:13,995
Behind you!

94
00:10:21,643 --> 00:10:23,167
I can't... move.

95
00:10:24,212 --> 00:10:25,736
What's this guy?

96
00:10:28,483 --> 00:10:31,418
I leave this to you, Sakon! Do it!

97
00:10:36,124 --> 00:10:37,557
<i>Where's the other one?</i>

98
00:10:38,193 --> 00:10:42,755
Hey! Who are you looking for?

99
00:10:44,265 --> 00:10:46,256
<i>That state... I know!</i>

100
00:10:47,001 --> 00:10:51,233
Be careful!
They enter the body and start to fuse!

101
00:10:51,906 --> 00:10:53,237
It's too late.

102
00:11:03,251 --> 00:11:04,275
This guy!

103
00:11:08,823 --> 00:11:10,256
What's the matter, Sakon?!

104
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:33,806
It seems like...

105
00:11:33,882 --> 00:11:36,976
your Jutsu didn't work...
on the puppet.

106
00:11:37,852 --> 00:11:39,183
<i>This is a puppet, too?!</i>

107
00:11:43,424 --> 00:11:44,482
Let me tell you this.

108
00:11:44,559 --> 00:11:48,791
We, the Sand Ninja,
aren't as lax as the Leaf.

109
00:11:49,063 --> 00:11:53,193
Moreover, don't be carelessly
approaching...

110
00:11:58,006 --> 00:11:59,234
the Black Ant!

111
00:12:04,579 --> 00:12:06,706
<i>He was fearsome</i>
<i>when he was an enemy...</i>

112
00:12:06,781 --> 00:12:09,944
<i>But to think he'd be this dependable</i>
<i>when becoming an ally.</i>

113
00:12:48,624 --> 00:12:53,254
Ow... I got careless.
Let me rest in your body for a bit.

114
00:12:53,629 --> 00:12:55,324
Good for nothing guy...

115
00:12:55,931 --> 00:12:57,592
Who are these guys?

116
00:12:57,933 --> 00:12:59,730
This is their ability!

117
00:13:00,769 --> 00:13:02,999
Although you were caught off guard...

118
00:13:03,139 --> 00:13:05,972
you getting hammered
by that puppet play...

119
00:13:06,809 --> 00:13:07,639
Well...

120
00:13:08,344 --> 00:13:11,575
Its power and speed
are nothing special.

121
00:13:11,647 --> 00:13:14,514
I won't be beaten
by the likes of such a toy.

122
00:13:23,125 --> 00:13:25,059
And I was able
to heal my belly wound.

123
00:13:26,896 --> 00:13:29,387
I don't have much Chakra left...
but well,

124
00:13:29,465 --> 00:13:33,731
these are opponents I should be able
to tear apart, nevertheless.

125
00:13:34,170 --> 00:13:38,971
<i>Indeed, it seems he's healed.</i>
<i>What a recovery ability he's got.</i>

126
00:13:42,378 --> 00:13:45,575
Ordinarily, I'm not the one
who becomes the main body,

127
00:13:45,648 --> 00:13:47,479
so it's hard to move, damn it.

128
00:13:48,584 --> 00:13:50,643
You sure are mocking us...

129
00:13:52,154 --> 00:13:54,452
He's not an opponent
you can beat fighting head on!

130
00:13:54,523 --> 00:13:55,990
We should retreat for now and...

131
00:13:58,194 --> 00:14:01,095
We can't back down after having been
mocked, you know.

132
00:14:12,541 --> 00:14:13,565
Don't mess with me!

133
00:14:38,601 --> 00:14:41,434
The Black Ant isn't a Mechanism
for attacking.

134
00:14:41,704 --> 00:14:44,138
Primarily, it's just for capturing.

135
00:14:44,974 --> 00:14:49,843
And... Crow paired up with the Black Ant
is exclusively for attacking.

136
00:14:50,546 --> 00:14:55,848
Hey you! Let me out!

137
00:15:19,742 --> 00:15:21,175
Eat this!

138
00:15:22,044 --> 00:15:23,443
Puppet Show...

139
00:15:23,879 --> 00:15:27,645
Hey, let me out! Let me out!

140
00:15:28,217 --> 00:15:30,913
Secret Black Move Iron Maiden!

141
00:15:58,347 --> 00:15:59,644
The play is over.

142
00:16:08,857 --> 00:16:10,722
She hid, huh...?

143
00:16:12,695 --> 00:16:13,923
Or did she run away?

144
00:16:14,463 --> 00:16:16,727
No... That couldn't be...

145
00:16:19,702 --> 00:16:21,636
I just got here.

146
00:16:22,137 --> 00:16:24,867
Briefly explain the present situation

147
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:27,909
including an analysis of her ability
and battle style.

148
00:16:28,877 --> 00:16:32,506
First off, her fundamental tactic is
ensnaring her opponent in Genjutsu

149
00:16:32,581 --> 00:16:34,139
with the sound of her flute.

150
00:16:34,450 --> 00:16:37,544
And then she delivers physical attacks
to that opening.

151
00:16:39,321 --> 00:16:41,812
<i>Demon Flute. Chains of Fantasia!</i>

152
00:16:48,364 --> 00:16:52,266
This is bad! Is this Genjutsu?

153
00:16:55,938 --> 00:16:58,406
I can't move my body...!

154
00:17:01,844 --> 00:17:04,836
<i>I believe this was your last hand, right?</i>

155
00:17:05,547 --> 00:17:07,708
<i>Unfortunately...</i>
<i>this is reversed checkmate!</i>

156
00:17:09,051 --> 00:17:10,109
<i>You little rat!</i>

157
00:17:11,019 --> 00:17:13,886
She's a classic Genjutsu style
distance range type.

158
00:17:14,757 --> 00:17:18,022
Most likely, she must've seen your Jutsu
and figured out immediately

159
00:17:18,093 --> 00:17:20,857
that it wouldn't mix well
with her own Jutsu.

160
00:17:21,163 --> 00:17:22,892
And it's two against one, too.

161
00:17:23,265 --> 00:17:27,725
She'll never appear before us again
until she casts her Genjutsu.

162
00:17:28,504 --> 00:17:29,402
Sound, huh...?

163
00:17:30,639 --> 00:17:31,298
Yeah...

164
00:17:34,443 --> 00:17:37,173
Genjutsu generally appeal
to the five senses of people...

165
00:17:37,246 --> 00:17:41,410
sight, hearing, smell, taste and touch.

166
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:48,650
The type that uses hearing
is the most troublesome of them all.

167
00:17:50,793 --> 00:17:56,527
After she cleverly takes a distance on you
and then hides...

168
00:17:56,598 --> 00:18:00,125
you have no idea where the Genjutsu
will be cast from or when.

169
00:18:01,570 --> 00:18:03,800
The idea is for us to already be cast
by the Genjutsu

170
00:18:03,872 --> 00:18:07,000
by the time we've figured out where she is
by the sound of the flute...

171
00:18:11,547 --> 00:18:12,673
Ouch...

172
00:18:14,016 --> 00:18:18,009
In my opinion, we're at an
overwhelming disadvantage.

173
00:18:19,621 --> 00:18:23,148
<i>A battle with this type, essentially,</i>
<i>wouldn't even be worth talking about</i>

174
00:18:23,225 --> 00:18:25,250
<i>without sensor types</i>
<i>like Kiba or Neji.</i>

175
00:18:27,062 --> 00:18:30,793
At this rate, we'll get pushed into a corner
sooner or later.

176
00:18:31,366 --> 00:18:34,529
- We should just retreat...
- Who asked for your opinion?!

177
00:18:36,171 --> 00:18:38,969
I told you to just explain the situation.

178
00:18:40,742 --> 00:18:44,838
Don't misjudge my power...

179
00:18:45,948 --> 00:18:48,508
If she thinks
she's hiding well from me...

180
00:18:48,584 --> 00:18:52,611
in a distance enough for the sound
of her flute to reach...

181
00:18:54,556 --> 00:18:55,784
she's naïve!

182
00:18:56,592 --> 00:19:00,392
Summoning: Blade Dance

183
00:19:03,065 --> 00:19:03,690
Cut!

184
00:19:13,876 --> 00:19:14,706
<i>All right...</i>

185
00:19:15,978 --> 00:19:18,469
<i>I've made it this far.</i>
<i>It's about time for my Genjutsu...</i>

186
00:19:19,581 --> 00:19:20,343
Huh?

187
00:20:09,097 --> 00:20:10,064
How about it?

188
00:20:11,099 --> 00:20:12,191
It's done.

189
00:20:14,603 --> 00:20:16,366
<i>She's sure...pushy.</i>

190
00:20:16,438 --> 00:20:20,135
<i>She's scarier than my mom.</i>

191
00:20:22,144 --> 00:20:23,441
Pretty good, huh?

192
00:20:25,247 --> 00:20:26,214
<i>But well...</i>

193
00:20:27,115 --> 00:20:30,346
<i>I just have to be grateful</i>
<i>for this time...huh?</i>

194
00:21:11,427 --> 00:21:13,827
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

195
00:21:13,896 --> 00:21:16,922
<i>And you smiled</i>

196
00:21:17,166 --> 00:21:19,464
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

197
00:21:19,535 --> 00:21:22,265
<i>In my own words</i>

198
00:21:22,338 --> 00:21:27,901
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

199
00:21:28,177 --> 00:21:33,444
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

200
00:21:33,716 --> 00:21:39,120
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

201
00:21:39,321 --> 00:21:44,850
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

202
00:21:45,761 --> 00:21:51,028
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

203
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:58,100
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

204
00:21:58,607 --> 00:22:01,303
<i>I feel so sad</i>

205
00:22:01,377 --> 00:22:02,275
<i>But...</i>

206
00:22:02,344 --> 00:22:04,744
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

207
00:22:04,813 --> 00:22:07,782
<i>And you smiled</i>

208
00:22:07,916 --> 00:22:10,510
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

209
00:22:10,586 --> 00:22:13,578
<i>In my own words</i>

210
00:22:13,756 --> 00:22:16,088
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

211
00:22:16,158 --> 00:22:19,286
<i>And you smiled</i>

212
00:22:19,361 --> 00:22:21,829
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

213
00:22:21,897 --> 00:22:24,798
<i>In my own words</i>

214
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:29,427
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

215
00:22:37,713 --> 00:22:41,149
I got careless earlier,
but it won't be like that now!

216
00:22:41,717 --> 00:22:43,446
Now, you please stand back.

217
00:22:44,053 --> 00:22:47,250
I'm grateful for the help,
but his opponent will be me!

218
00:22:47,823 --> 00:22:49,620
Next, for sure,
with my ultimate Lotus...!

219
00:22:50,693 --> 00:22:56,461
Hey, why are you moving forward?
I'm his opponent!

220
00:22:57,766 --> 00:23:01,600
Next episode,
"Showdown: Gaara vs. Kimimaro!"
